    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Is Murder Justified?</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Bee Hoffman letter responds to Jan 22 editorial criticizing Federal Judge John E Sprizzo's decision exonerating anti-abortion protesters, Brother Christopher Moscinski and retired Bishop George E Lynch, from criminal contempt charges</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re Judge John E. Sprizzo's justification of breaking the law for reasons of religious conviction (editorial, Jan. 22): Does he excuse the murder of Prime Minister Yitzhak Rabin of Israel on the same grounds?</p>
        <p>BEE HOFFMAN</p>
        <p>Verona, N.J., Jan. 22, 1997</p>
      </block>
